Study type
=================
Interventional

Description
=================
This is a single-arm, single-center, open-label, multi-stage clinical trial.

In the induction stage, patients are treated for 6 cycles. If the overall response rate (ORR) >= 10% at stage 1a, or ORR >= 15% at stage 1b. The dose may be escalated to the next level in stage 1c until the maximum dose is reached. In each stage, the dose is escalated for a maximum of 6 new enrollment patients. If the maximum dose is reached or the ORR is less than 15% at stage 1c, the dose will be reduced to the next lower dose level for evaluation.   
In the expansion stage, patients will be continued to receive the established dose in the future. A total of 15 patients with advanced NSCLC (including squamous cell carcinoma and non-squamous cell carcinoma) are planned to participate in the expansion stage.
